					<head>Liturgy</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/n80040114" rend="visible">
						<summary>Festival prayer book (maḥzor) for Rosh ha-Shanah and Yom Kipur, and beginning of Sukot, Ashkenazi rite (aka 'Dragon's Head Maḥzor').</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he"/>
						<msItem n="0" rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/n80040114">
							<locus from="1r" to="163v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Maḥzor</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">מחזור</title>
							<note>
								<p>See further <ref target="Davidson_1924"/> and Sarit Shalev-Eyni, 'Ashkenazi Illuminated Manuscripts in the British Isles', New Letter of the Center for Jewish Art 12 (1996), http://cja.huji.ac.il/NL12-HIMBI.htm (accessed on 26 September 2014).</p>
							</note>
							<decoNote type="border">Text framed by and arch inhabited by hybrids in ink. <locus n="58r"/>
							</decoNote>
							<decoNote type="initial">11 inhabited initial words in ink and sometimes with red. <locus n="1r, 10v, 17v, 26v, 30r, 44v, 46r, 58r, 58v, 110r, 140v"/>
							</decoNote>
							<decoNote type="illustration">Image of a hybrid next to an initial word in ink. <locus n="27v"/>
							</decoNote>
							<decoNote type="illustration">3 drawings in ink next to the catchwords.<locus n="51v, 59v, 163v"/>
							</decoNote>
							<decoNote type="illustration">Drawings of small dragon heads in ink decorating the first letters of lines on 12 folios.<locus n="47r, 53r, 61r, 62r, 63r, 64r, 78r, 78v, 79r, 79v, 126r, 144v"/>
							</decoNote>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="1r" to="26r"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Services for the first day of Rosh ha-Shanah</title>
							<note>
								<p>Shaḥarit begins on folio 1r, musaf starts on folio 10r.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="26r" to="44v"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Services for the second day of Rosh ha-Shanah</title>
							<note>
								<p>Shaḥarit begins on folio 26r, musaf begins on folio 37r.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="44v" to="163v"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Services for Yom Kipur</title>
							<note>
								<p>Ma῾ariv begins on folio 44v, shaḥarit on folio 58r, musaf on folio 110r, and minḥah on folio 143r, ne῾ilah on folio 158r.</p>
								<p>Folio 163v contains the beginning of shaḥarit for Sukot.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex of the last quarter of the 14th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<support>Parchment.</support>
								<extent>163 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>435</height>
										<width>310</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>270/265</height>
										<width>200/190</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>163 folios (+ 3 unfoliated modern paper flyleaves at the beginning and 4 unfoliated modern paper flyleaves at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>20 quires: i8 (folios 1-8), ii8-1 (folios 9-15), iii8 (folios 16-23), iv8 (folios 24-31), v10 (folios 32-41), vi10 (folios 42-51), vii-xii8 (folios 52-99), xiii10 (folios 100-109), xiv8 (folios 110-117), xv8 (folios 118-125), xvi10 (folios 126-135), xvii8-1 (folios 136-142), xviii8 (folios 143-150), xix5 (folios 151-155), xx8 (folios 156-163).</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>First few leaves damaged.</p>
									<p>Defective at the beginning and at the end.</p>
									<p>Lower margin has been cut off numerous times (folios 56, 57, 84, 86, 87, 105, 119, 125, 126, 127, 131, 149, 152). </p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="27" writtenLines="26">
									<p>Uniform layout.</p>
									<p>Visible pricking and hard-point ruling.</p>
									<p>Initial words written in larger characters.</p>
									<p>Hair side and flesh side are distinguishable.</p>
									<p>Several marginal notes in a semi-cursive script.</p>
									<p>Erasures (e.g., folios 81v, 85r) or passages drawn across (e.g., folios 18r, 24v, 25r, 35v, 87v, 102r, 108v, 109v, 121r, 121v, 128v, 158r), entire poem drawn across (folios 96v-97r, 98r-99r, 99r-99v, 153v).</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Ashkenazi square script, partially punctuated. <name type="person" role="scribe">Avraham</name>?: the name Avraham is marked on folio 110r.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="major"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>The word ‘Moie’ is written in Latin characters in the upper margin of folio 68v, and ‘Mojs’ in the upper margin of folio 107v.</p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
